Governor Okoth Obado of Migori in south-western and his two aides will remain in custody for several more days after the High Court set their bail hearing for this Friday. The High Court has allowed the State to merge their murder cases over the killing of Rongo University student Sharon Otieno. Counts of murder Mr Obado, his personal assistant Michael Juma Oyamo and a County Assembly clerk Casper Obiero pleaded to the charges again on Monday at the Milimani Law Courts. The three have been charged with two counts of murder, that of killing Ms Otieno and her unborn child.   Okoth Obado applies for bail to continue with his gubernatorial job. October 10 holiday to be observed following court ruling Water supply disrupted after pipes are ripped apart